task.summary:
Can now switch between maps in a 2 way fashion. not 1 way.
Player is drawn ,animated and collision logic is accounted for more logically now that we are using the current instance of the player
Cooldown for switching between maps and the player does not switch when standing in a gate.
Rewrote comments to make more sense
Removed all tile-based movement for the player as tile-based movement will not be used for this project.
draws hitboxes around gates as well
moved keypress.py into mechanics
created grey maps for extra testing and to reduce the risk of seizures due to the other maps being quite bright and flashy.

modified testing stuffs.py to better search directories
also added a logs text file. might come in handy

modified testing stuffs.py to better search directories
also added a logs text file. might come in handy
map metadata files are revamped -renamed variable names to be more intuitive -made a template meta file -made a full template meta map layout (issue: backdrop edge detection makes the fps drop hard)
draws player at gate locations upon entering a new area instead of the middle -need to work on backdrop movement checking -otherwise the player was drawn at a distance from the gate
added a dialogue system -plan to allow textboxes can be customized with an added json and external files(png for textbox, font and colour) -made progress on audio, but linux audio drivers are problematic
